Author: jl777c#5810
Content: native wallet is more secure than lite wallet

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: but more importantly it is more reliable as it doesnt rely on external servers

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: a fake SPV server can try to convince you that you received funds that you didnt actually receive

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: it cant take away your funds, but it could make you think you got somethiing and then you send in response to that. it would require taking over all the spv servers you are using and having yourself specifically targeted. essentially the same thing can be done to a native node via eclipse attack, but that is  harder to do

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: so i guess lite wallets are less secure in that it is easier to conduct an eclipse attack against it than a native node, not that an eclipse attack is easy to do, just easier

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: so it is more a secure vs more secure

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: now if you are cross checking things locally, along with an explorer that isnt corrupted, then the eclipse attack doesnt work
